abstract: After the assertions from his national security adviser, the president appeared resigned to the possibility of witnesses, peopel close to him said.
snippet: After the assertions from his national security adviser, the president appeared resigned to the possibility of witnesses, peopel close to him said.
lead_paragraph: President Trump believes the chances that witnesses will be called at his impeachment trial in the Senate have grown, even as advisers believed they might be able to allay concerns from senators after reports about assertions made by his former national security adviser, John R. Bolton, in an unpublished manuscript.
headline_main: Trump sees witnesses as increasingly likely.

abstract: Despite pro-Trump programming in the mornings and prime-time, Fox News has irked Mr. Trump when he detects any hint of disloyalty.
snippet: Despite pro-Trump programming in the mornings and prime-time, Fox News has irked Mr. Trump when he detects any hint of disloyalty.
lead_paragraph: One loyal Fox News viewer is not thrilled about the network’s impeachment coverage.
headline_main: Television critic in chief attacks Fox.

abstract: “It’s an embarrassing day for Harvard Law School,” Senator Sheldon Whitehouse, Democrat of Rhode Island, said.
snippet: “It’s an embarrassing day for Harvard Law School,” Senator Sheldon Whitehouse, Democrat of Rhode Island, said.
lead_paragraph: Tell us how you really feel about Alan Dershowitz, Democrats.

abstract: President Donald Trump has nominated a former Tennessee House speaker to serve on the board of directors of the nation's largest public utility.

lead_paragraph: NASHVILLE, Tenn. — President Donald Trump has nominated a former Tennessee House speaker to serve on the board of directors of the nation's largest public utility.

abstract: Here is a look at the opposing legal teams.
snippet: Here is a look at the opposing legal teams.
lead_paragraph: For the third time in American history, the Senate has convened as a court of impeachment to consider whether to remove a sitting president, and two teams of lawyers are facing off in a confrontation with heavy political and constitutional consequences.
headline_main: A look at the impeachment teams in their own words.

abstract: “This idea of bargaining — ‘Well, we’ll give you one irrelevant witness for one material witness’ — baloney,” Senator Dick Durbin said.
snippet: “This idea of bargaining — ‘Well, we’ll give you one irrelevant witness for one material witness’ — baloney,” Senator Dick Durbin said.
lead_paragraph: As Republicans face mounting pressure to subpoena new witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial, Democratic senators are again rejecting the idea of a deal that would schedule depositions from John R. Bolton, the president’s former national security adviser, in exchange for a witness that Mr. Trump wants, like Hunter Biden, the son of the former vice president.

abstract: In Arizona, where elections are getting closer, a federal appeals court undid strict limits on ballot collection and votes cast at the wrong precinct.
snippet: In Arizona, where elections are getting closer, a federal appeals court undid strict limits on ballot collection and votes cast at the wrong precinct.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — If a voter accidentally casts a ballot in the wrong precinct, should it be counted? Should early voters be able to give their sealed ballots to someone else to drop in the mail or deliver to a polling place?

abstract: Republican U.S. Rep. Doug Collins said “there will be more coming later” about his expected Senate bid, otherwise keeping quiet about the race during a visit Tuesday to the Georgia state Capitol as lawmakers advanced a bill that could give the congressman an edge if he decides to challenge newly sworn-in GOP Sen. Kelly Loeffler.

lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Republican U.S. Rep. Doug Collins said “there will be more coming later” about his expected Senate bid, otherwise keeping quiet about the race during a visit Tuesday to the Georgia state Capitol as lawmakers advanced a bill that could give the congressman an edge if he decides to challenge newly sworn-in GOP Sen. Kelly Loeffler.
headline_main: Collins Quiet on Georgia Senate During State Capitol Stop
headline_print_headline: Collins Quiet on Georgia Senate During State Capitol Stop
